4 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
5 Sec. 1. 20 V.S.A. § 4652 is amended to read:
6 § 4652. AUTHORIZATION TO ENTER INTO AGREEMENTS
7 PURSUANT TO 8 U.S.C. § 1357(g) AND 19 U.S.C. § 1401(i)
8 (a) Notwithstanding any other provision of law, only the Governor, in
9 consultation with the Vermont Attorney General, is authorized to enter into,
10 modify, or extend an agreement pursuant to 8 U.S.C. § 1357(g) or 19 U.S.C.
11 § 1401(i).
12 (b) Notwithstanding subsection (a) of this section, a State, county, or
13 municipal law enforcement agency is authorized to enter into an agreement
14 pursuant to 8 U.S.C. § 1357(g) or 19 U.S.C. § 1401(i) when necessary to
15 address threats to the public safety or welfare of Vermont residents arising out
16 of a declaration of a State or national emergency No public agency, as that
17 term is defined in 1 V.S.A. § 317, or an officer, employee, agent, or
18 independent contractor of a public agency, shall enter into an agreement
19 pursuant to 8 U.S.C. § 1357(g) or 19 U.S.C. § 1401(i) unless the Governor has
20 authorized the agreement as set forth in subsection (a) of this section.
